CONTINUING the discussion from a few days ago:
WHICH way to cope?
We all wish for anthros - our waifurs, to be real. But this will never happen. I knew this anon once, whose sole dream in life was to make anthros real. He was really serious about it, and was in the bio-something field. In all honesty, I don't think he can succeed. But I truly hope he will.
So anthros as we know them will likely never be real, at least in our lifetime. So all we can do is cope.
WHICH way?
a.) Escapism - you draw, write, look at drawing and read. Discuss /hmofa/ with fellow anons. You will live your life lonely. There is a void in your heart.
b.) Escapism, but even further. Bring your waifur to life as a tulpa, live your life in your mind-world. You will live your life lonely, but you will feel nothing like it. You at least feel like she's real. There is a void in your heart.
c.) Marry a femanon who is a furry. Live a normal life except sometimes she wears a convincing fursuit. You won't be lonely, and you might have the lovelife you desire. But it will never be the same. There is a void in your heart.
These three are all known. But is there... a fourth way?

"they as a singular pronoun"

Yes, "they" can be used as a singular, gender indefinite pronoun. It's a fairly recent development in English to see it as commonly as we do, but it's been a grammar hack for a long time, like a century or more. And, it is a grammar hack, invented to fill a role unforeseen back into Shakespeare's time when gender-centric languages like German & Spanish insisted on assigning a male or female pronoun to objects such as trees and rocks.

It's not about having dreams. It's about remembering them. The best and most reliable way is to slightly wake up before schedule by a few hours and going back to sleep. That way you are half-awake and what you dream of sticks in your memory for a while longer. You should write down what you dream of too because it has a tendency to fleet away very fast.

I don't recommend it if you have early responsibilities or a good schedule though, since waking up early can just simply wake you up without being able to go back to sleep
